# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Pose Royale — environment template
#
# Usage:
#   cp apps/web/.env.example apps/web/.env.local
#   # fill in values → restart `pnpm dev`
#
# `.env.local` is gitignored at the repo root. Only variables prefixed with
# `VITE_` are exposed to the browser bundle — everything in this file is
# shipped to the client, so never put a *true* secret here. Keys for services
# like Firebase are designed to be public; access control happens via that
# service's security rules, not via hiding the key.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── Firebase (multiplayer rooms, presence, ELO, leaderboard) ─────────────────
# Firebase Console → Project Settings → Your apps → Web → SDK snippet → Config.
# All seven values are needed for a "full" client; only `databaseURL` is
# strictly required by Pose Royale (plan §5 — we use Realtime Database for
# room state and WebRTC signaling).
#
# Security model (important): treat these as public identifiers. The real
# gate is your RTDB security rules — lock writes to authenticated clients and
# validate schemas there before shipping to production.
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project
VITE_FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL=https://your-project-default-rtdb.firebaseio.com
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=


# ── WebRTC ICE / TURN (opponent video bubble NAT traversal) ──────────────────
# Google STUN alone reaches ~80% of home networks. The remaining 20% (symmetric
# NATs, corporate firewalls, some mobile carriers) need a TURN relay. We use
# Metered.ca — paid, well-priced, global.
#
# Option A — dynamic credentials (recommended by Metered):
#   Client fetches short-lived TURN creds per session from
#   https://<SUBDOMAIN>.metered.live/api/v1/turn/credentials?apiKey=<KEY>.
#   Credentials rotate, so a leaked bundle stops working after the TTL expires.
# VITE_METERED_SUBDOMAIN=poseroyale
# VITE_METERED_API_KEY=
#
# Option B — static creds (simpler, rotate manually):
#   Paste the "Static credentials" block from the Metered dashboard.
#   Comma-separate multiple URLs; the browser will try each in order.
# VITE_TURN_URLS=turn:global.turn.metered.ca:80,turn:global.turn.metered.ca:80?transport=tcp,turn:global.turn.metered.ca:443,turns:global.turn.metered.ca:443?transport=tcp
# VITE_TURN_USERNAME=
# VITE_TURN_CREDENTIAL=


# ── LearnSign detector backend (single-player, fully optional) ───────────────
# Default is `heuristic` — no TF.js, no downloads, no training. See
# apps/web/public/models/learnsign/README.md for the image vs. landmark trade-off.
# VITE_LEARNSIGN_BACKEND=heuristic
# VITE_LEARNSIGN_IMAGE_MODEL_URL=/models/learnsign/model.json
# VITE_LEARNSIGN_MODEL_URL=/models/learnsign/sign-classifier/model.json
